            <title>[PIG-2027] NPE if Pig don&apos;t have permission for log file</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2027</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If specify a log file to Pig, but Pig don&apos;t have write permission, if any failure in Pig script, we will get a NPE in addition to Pig script failure:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2011-05-02 13:18:36,493 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;main&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ERROR org.apache.pig.tools.grunt.Grunt - java.lang.NullPointerException&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.pig.impl.util.LogUtils.writeLog(LogUtils.java:172)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.pig.impl.util.LogUtils.writeLog(LogUtils.java:79)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.pig.tools.grunt.GruntParser.executeBatch(GruntParser.java:131)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.pig.tools.grunt.GruntParser.parseStopOnError(GruntParser.java:180)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.pig.tools.grunt.GruntParser.parseStopOnError(GruntParser.java:152)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.pig.tools.grunt.Grunt.exec(Grunt.java:90)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.pig.Main.run(Main.java:554)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.pig.Main.main(Main.java:109)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
